==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tarsius
<hw>Tar"si*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Tarsus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of nocturnal
lemurine mammals having very large eyes and ears, a long tail, and very
long proximal tarsal bones; -- called also <altname>malmag</altname>,
<altname>spectral lemur</altname>, <altname>podji</altname>, and
<altname>tarsier</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tarso-</ent>⟦br⟧
